• Flutterwave, Opay, Andela join Interswitch, Jumia The Nigerian FinTech ecosystem maintained its growth trajectory within the African continent with three more unicorns – Flutterwave, OPay and Andela – joining Interswitch and Jumia as five out of the seven unicorns on the continent.
    
According to FinTechNGR, Nigeria’s fintech association, which disclosed this, noted that Nigeria’s FinTech ecosystem’s stronger and improved brand appeal to global investors, showed that the country is an economy positioned for growth, financial inclusion and a narrowing poverty gap.
   
FinTechNGR, in a document, said Nigeria was ranked as sixth in real-time payments by Finshots, and also as one of the top crypto trading countries in the world by Statista, amongst other ground-breaking feats, which attest to the value of the country’s ecosystem.  FinTechNGR noted that the launch of eNaira by the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) showed that innovation is not limited to FinTech firms alone  – rather, regulators are now also actively taking part in the next digital wave, thereby opening up more opportunities for entrepreneurs to innovate. 